34// Bits for subtarget features that participate in instruction matching.
35enum SubtargetFeatureBits : uint8_t {
36 Feature_In32BitModeBit = 1,
37 Feature_In64BitModeBit = 9,
38 Feature_HasOnlyMSYNCBit = 21,
39 Feature_HasSYNCBit = 20,
40 Feature_HasSPEBit = 8,
41 Feature_HasICBTBit = 19,
42 Feature_HasBPERMDBit = 10,
43 Feature_HasExtDivBit = 3,
44 Feature_IsISA3_0Bit = 2,
45 Feature_HasFPUBit = 0,
46 Feature_PCRelativeMemopsBit = 29,
47 Feature_IsNotISA3_1Bit = 30,
48 Feature_HasAltivecBit = 4,
49 Feature_HasP8AltivecBit = 5,
50 Feature_HasP8CryptoBit = 6,
51 Feature_HasP9AltivecBit = 7,
52 Feature_HasVSXBit = 11,
53 Feature_IsLittleEndianBit = 22,
54 Feature_IsBigEndianBit = 23,
55 Feature_IsPPC64Bit = 25,
56 Feature_HasOnlySwappingMemOpsBit = 12,
57 Feature_HasP8VectorBit = 13,
58 Feature_HasDirectMoveBit = 14,
59 Feature_NoP9VectorBit = 24,
60 Feature_HasP9VectorBit = 15,
61 Feature_NoP9AltivecBit = 26,
62 Feature_HasHTMBit = 27,
63 Feature_PrefixInstrsBit = 17,
64 Feature_IsISA3_1Bit = 18,
65 Feature_PairedVectorMemopsBit = 28,
66 Feature_MMABit = 16,
67};
68
69PredicateBitset PPCInstructionSelector::
70computeAvailableModuleFeatures(const PPCSubtarget *Subtarget) const {
71 PredicateBitset Features;
72 if (!Subtarget->isPPC64())
73 Features.set(Feature_In32BitModeBit);
74 if (Subtarget->isPPC64())
75 Features.set(Feature_In64BitModeBit);
76 if (Subtarget->hasOnlyMSYNC())
77 Features.set(Feature_HasOnlyMSYNCBit);
78 if (!Subtarget->hasOnlyMSYNC())
79 Features.set(Feature_HasSYNCBit);
80 if (Subtarget->hasSPE())
81 Features.set(Feature_HasSPEBit);
82 if (Subtarget->hasICBT())
83 Features.set(Feature_HasICBTBit);
84 if (Subtarget->hasBPERMD())
85 Features.set(Feature_HasBPERMDBit);
86 if (Subtarget->hasExtDiv())
87 Features.set(Feature_HasExtDivBit);
88 if (Subtarget->isISA3_0())
89 Features.set(Feature_IsISA3_0Bit);
90 if (Subtarget->hasFPU())
91 Features.set(Feature_HasFPUBit);
92 if (Subtarget->hasPCRelativeMemops())
93 Features.set(Feature_PCRelativeMemopsBit);
94 if (!Subtarget->isISA3_1())
95 Features.set(Feature_IsNotISA3_1Bit);
96 if (Subtarget->hasAltivec())
97 Features.set(Feature_HasAltivecBit);
98 if (Subtarget->hasP8Altivec())
99 Features.set(Feature_HasP8AltivecBit);
100 if (Subtarget->hasP8Crypto())
101 Features.set(Feature_HasP8CryptoBit);
102 if (Subtarget->hasP9Altivec())
103 Features.set(Feature_HasP9AltivecBit);
104 if (Subtarget->hasVSX())
105 Features.set(Feature_HasVSXBit);
106 if (Subtarget->isLittleEndian())
107 Features.set(Feature_IsLittleEndianBit);
108 if (!Subtarget->isLittleEndian())
109 Features.set(Feature_IsBigEndianBit);
110 if (Subtarget->isPPC64())
111 Features.set(Feature_IsPPC64Bit);
112 if (!Subtarget->hasP9Vector())
113 Features.set(Feature_HasOnlySwappingMemOpsBit);
114 if (Subtarget->hasP8Vector())
115 Features.set(Feature_HasP8VectorBit);
116 if (Subtarget->hasDirectMove())
117 Features.set(Feature_HasDirectMoveBit);
118 if (!Subtarget->hasP9Vector())
119 Features.set(Feature_NoP9VectorBit);
120 if (Subtarget->hasP9Vector())
121 Features.set(Feature_HasP9VectorBit);
122 if (!Subtarget->hasP9Altivec())
123 Features.set(Feature_NoP9AltivecBit);
124 if (Subtarget->hasHTM())
125 Features.set(Feature_HasHTMBit);
126 if (Subtarget->hasPrefixInstrs())
127 Features.set(Feature_PrefixInstrsBit);
128 if (Subtarget->isISA3_1())
129 Features.set(Feature_IsISA3_1Bit);
130 if (Subtarget->pairedVectorMemops())
131 Features.set(Feature_PairedVectorMemopsBit);
132 if (Subtarget->hasMMA())
133 Features.set(Feature_MMABit);
134 return Features;
135}

137void PPCInstructionSelector::setupGeneratedPerFunctionState(MachineFunction &MF) {
138 AvailableFunctionFeatures = computeAvailableFunctionFeatures((const PPCSubtarget *)&MF.getSubtarget(), &MF);
139}
140PredicateBitset PPCInstructionSelector::
141computeAvailableFunctionFeatures(const PPCSubtarget *Subtarget, const MachineFunction *MF) const {
142 PredicateBitset Features;
143 return Features;
144}

225// PatFrag predicates.
226enum {
227 GIPFP_I64_Predicate_Msk2Imm = GIPFP_I64_Invalid + 1,
228 GIPFP_I64_Predicate_Msk4Imm,
229 GIPFP_I64_Predicate_Msk8Imm,
230 GIPFP_I64_Predicate_i32immNonAllOneNonZero,
231 GIPFP_I64_Predicate_imm32SExt16,
232 GIPFP_I64_Predicate_imm64SExt16,
233 GIPFP_I64_Predicate_imm64ZExt32,
234 GIPFP_I64_Predicate_immNonAllOneAnyExt8,
235 GIPFP_I64_Predicate_immSExt5NonZero,
236};
237bool PPCInstructionSelector::testImmPredicate_I64(unsigned PredicateID, int64_t Imm) const {
238 switch (PredicateID) {
239 case GIPFP_I64_Predicate_Msk2Imm: {
240 return isUInt<2>(Imm);
241 llvm_unreachable("ImmediateCode should have returned");
242 return false;
243 }
244 case GIPFP_I64_Predicate_Msk4Imm: {
245 return isUInt<4>(Imm);
246 llvm_unreachable("ImmediateCode should have returned");
247 return false;
248 }
249 case GIPFP_I64_Predicate_Msk8Imm: {
250 return isUInt<8>(Imm);
251 llvm_unreachable("ImmediateCode should have returned");
252 return false;
253 }
254 case GIPFP_I64_Predicate_i32immNonAllOneNonZero: {
255 return Imm && (Imm != -1);
256 llvm_unreachable("ImmediateCode should have returned");
257 return false;
258 }
259 case GIPFP_I64_Predicate_imm32SExt16: {
260
261 // imm32SExt16 predicate - True if the i32 immediate fits in a 16-bit
262 // sign extended field. Used by instructions like 'addi'.
263 return (int32_t)Imm == (short)Imm;
264
265 llvm_unreachable("ImmediateCode should have returned");
266 return false;
267 }
268 case GIPFP_I64_Predicate_imm64SExt16: {
269
270 // imm64SExt16 predicate - True if the i64 immediate fits in a 16-bit
271 // sign extended field. Used by instructions like 'addi'.
272 return (int64_t)Imm == (short)Imm;
273
274 llvm_unreachable("ImmediateCode should have returned");
275 return false;
276 }
277 case GIPFP_I64_Predicate_imm64ZExt32: {
278
279 // imm64ZExt32 predicate - True if the i64 immediate fits in a 32-bit
280 // zero extended field.
281 return isUInt<32>(Imm);
282
283 llvm_unreachable("ImmediateCode should have returned");
284 return false;
285 }
286 case GIPFP_I64_Predicate_immNonAllOneAnyExt8: {
287
288 return (isInt<8>(Imm) && (Imm != -1)) || (isUInt<8>(Imm) && (Imm != 0xFF));
289
290 llvm_unreachable("ImmediateCode should have returned");
291 return false;
292 }
293 case GIPFP_I64_Predicate_immSExt5NonZero: {
294 return Imm && isInt<5>(Imm);
295 llvm_unreachable("ImmediateCode should have returned");
296 return false;
297 }
298 }
299 llvm_unreachable("Unknown predicate");
300 return false;
301}
302bool PPCInstructionSelector::testImmPredicate_APFloat(unsigned PredicateID, const APFloat & Imm) const {
303 llvm_unreachable("Unknown predicate");
304 return false;
305}
306bool PPCInstructionSelector::testImmPredicate_APInt(unsigned PredicateID, const APInt & Imm) const {
307 llvm_unreachable("Unknown predicate");
308 return false;

310bool PPCInstructionSelector::testMIPredicate_MI(unsigned PredicateID, const MachineInstr & MI, const std::array<const MachineOperand *, 3> &Operands) const {
311 const MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent();
312 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
313 (void)MRI;
314 llvm_unreachable("Unknown predicate");
315 return false;
316}

332bool PPCInstructionSelector::selectImpl(MachineInstr &I, CodeGenCoverage &CoverageInfo) const {
333 MachineFunction &MF = *I.getParent()->getParent();
334 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
335 const PredicateBitset AvailableFeatures = getAvailableFeatures();
336 NewMIVector OutMIs;
337 State.MIs.clear();
338 State.MIs.push_back(&I);
339
340 if (executeMatchTable(*this, OutMIs, State, ISelInfo, getMatchTable(), TII, MRI, TRI, RBI, AvailableFeatures, CoverageInfo)) {
341 return true;
342 }
343
344 return false;
345}

13039PredicateBitset AvailableModuleFeatures;

13041PredicateBitset getAvailableFeatures() const {
13042 return AvailableModuleFeatures | AvailableFunctionFeatures;
13043}
